    <h1 id="title">Selecting the Right Program for You</h1>
    <div id="content_container">
        <h2><a name="section5"></a>5.  Relevant Questions</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>What are the main differences among the five general types of program sponsors?</li>
            <li>Can you identify which one of the five general types of program sponsors your program has and why you prefer that type of program?</li>
            <li>What kind of relationship does your home college/university have with the study abroad program in the country of your choice?</li>
            <li>How long has the program been in existence (a new program doesn't necessarily mean a bad program)?</li>
            <li>What is the program's current financial situation?</li>
        </ul>
        <h2><a name="section6"></a>6.  Checklist</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>  I have asked my program's administrators how closely my U.S. home college/university will be working with my program coordinators in the country of your choice.</li>
            <li>I know which of the five types of program sponsors runs my study abroad program.</li>
            <li>I am aware of what kind of facilities my program has in the country of your choice (i.e. a one person office versus a comprehensive campus).</li>
            <li>I know whether I will be enrolled in a foreign university, a U.S. university or an independent program in the country of your choice.</li>
  I understand what services and activities will and will not be provided for me by my program.</li>
        </ul>
